          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Tesla’s absence in India has allowed competitors like Maruti Suzuki, BYD, and VinFast to <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-17-01-2025-wn1-3-seize-opportunity" target="_blank">seize opportunities</a> in the fast-growing EV market. At the Bharat Mobility Global Expo, Maruti debuted its e-Vitara SUV, joining Tata Motors, which leads with 60% of the market. High import taxes have deterred Tesla from expanding in the Indian market. The country’s EV market remains small at 2.4% of total car sales but is set for growth as automakers expand offerings to meet decarbonization goals.</p>
