            <strong>🇬🇧 UK’s buy-now-pay-later boom continues</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">BNPL services are gaining momentum in the UK. The model is becoming increasingly appealing to consumers as it allows easy purchases online <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-17-01-2025-wn2-4-without-interest-or-credit-checks" target="_blank">without interest or credit checks</a>. The market grew nearly a fifth to about $27 billion last year, putting it at 7.7% of the UK’s total e-commerce market  The market is currently dominated by major players like Klarna and Affirm. The government is getting ready to regulate the sector, with upcoming regulations aiming to level the playing field and ensure affordability checks.</p>
