          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Rio Tinto and Glencore are in early talks about merging. The merger could potentially create a mining giant that rivals BHP. The deal could combine their strong <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-17-01-2025-wn3-5-copper-assets" target="_blank">copper assets</a> but faces challenges due to Glencore’s coal business and regulatory scrutiny. The merger would align with the industry’s focus on copper for decarbonization. The deal is made more complex by the fact that Rio has pivoted toward cleaner metals of late while Glencore remains tied to coal.</p>
