        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-jan-17-3.jpg" alt="What is the Pigovian tax?" href="https://www.longandshort.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">A Pigovian tax is a tax on activities that harm society, like pollution. It’s designed to discourage harmful behavior by making it more expensive, helping to fix market problems and protect public well-being. For example, a carbon tax raises the cost of burning fossil fuels, encouraging people and businesses to use cleaner energy and reduce greenhouse gas emissions. Similarly, taxes on cigarettes or sugary drinks aim to lower consumption, improving public health.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Pigovian taxes are efficient because they make businesses and individuals consider the full cost of their actions, including the harm to society. They can help protect the environment, improve health, and provide government revenue for public programs.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
